  "secText": [
    "  <b class=\"object-name\">Supplemental Material: </b>  <span class=\"object-name\">Advanced Topic</span>",
    "  <b>Essential Question: </b>  <br />How can we identify single-slit diffraction?",
    "  <b>Enduring Understandings:</b>  <b>    <br />  </b>1. Light interference patterns caused by <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='18' data-topic='3' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='0'>single-slit diffraction</a> cause a large central band, with light bands that fade the farther they are from the central band. Just as in double-slit diffraction, in single-slit diffraction, constructive interference causes bright bands, and destructive interference causes dark bands.",
    "  <b>STEM Skills:</b>  <b>    <br />  </b>1. Review <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='18' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='2' data-subsection='0'>constructive</a> and <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='18' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='2' data-subsection='1'>destructive interference</a>.<br />2. Review <a class='pjumpToTopic' href='javascript:void(0)' data-chap='18' data-topic='0' data-subtopic='1' data-subsection='2'>light interference patterns</a>."
